answers.answer: Yep I am due to early pregnancies.
I am considered high risk. I have a bicorunate uterus. I have to see a specialist every two to three weeks to monitor my son's growth. I'm at risk for preterm labor.

I'm high risk because i had a cone biopsy done when i was a couple weeks pregnant (before myself or the Dr's knew). It's where they cut off a cone shaped piece of your cervix. So far so good. I have had zero complications. I'm 25 weeks
I'm 22 y/o, 14+2 weeks pregnant... Type 1 Diabetes (I use a lot of insulin) and Overweight... (considered morbid obesity) The baby is perfect, had appointenton Thursday
